description: Russian infantry are advancing inside the city, one of the last major urban centers in the Donetsk region still under Kyiv's control. Moscow's shift in tactics – focusing on destroying Ukrainian logistics – has paid off after six months.

headline: In Latvia, public mobilization continues to grow in support of the Istanbul Convention for preventing violence against women
description: Latvian lawmakers voted on October 30 to withdraw from the Istanbul Convention. Since then, the president has called for a review of the bill, as protests are planned across the country on Thursday.

headline: COP30: Optimistic Brazil seeks to secure concrete progress on climate action
description: The South American giant hopes to bridge emerging and wealthy nations, focusing on enforcing past COP pledges. But Brazil will need strong diplomacy to keep climate cooperation alive amid global tensions.

headline: Secluded Kalash tribe fights for survival in Pakistan
description: This ethnic and religious minority now numbers just 4,000 members and faces intrusive tourism and the degradation of their environment, which is essential to their survival.

headline: Too old to get a job, too young to retire: The French women over 50 stuck in limbo
description: In France, 21% of people aged 55-61 struggle to find work but are unable to retire. Women, who suffer more from societal inequalities throughout their career, are particularly at risk.

headline: A tunnel between Morocco and Spain, an old dream revived
description: Since the 19th century, the idea of a fixed link between Morocco and Europe has seen slow but steady progress. If realized, the project could transform the movement of people and goods across the western Mediterranean.
